Transport minister Fikile Mbalula says construction work on the new Msikaba Bridge is making steady progress. In a series of posts on social media., Mbalula shared new photos of the bridge which forms part of the new N2 Wild Coast Road project in KwaZulu-Natal and the Eastern Cape, “The (Msikaba Bridge) will stimulate investment and growth, initiate new economic sectors and transform the connection of rural communities to urban centres around the country,” he said. “The project will continue to create thousands of new jobs and economic opportunities in line with the new Economic Reconstruction and Recovery Plan.” <img class="aligncenter wp-image-596462 size-large" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-1-1024x674.png" alt="" width="840" height="553" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-1-1024x674.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-1-300x197.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-1-768x506.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-1-1200x790.png 1200w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-1.png 1261w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-596464 size-large" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-2-1024x734.png" alt="" width="840" height="602" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-2-1024x734.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-2-300x215.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-2-768x550.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Msikaba-2.png 1171w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-596466 size-large" src="h